.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "August 2024" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A basic command-line interpreter.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic command-line interpreter that provides a user interface to execute commands. It handles user input, parses commands, and executes them by forking child processes.

.SH USAGE
.TP
.B simple_shell
Launches the shell in an interactive mode where it waits for user commands indefinitely.

.SH COMMANDS
.PP
The following commands are supported:
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell program.
.TP
.B any other command
Any valid command available on the system is executed.

.SH FUNCTIONS
.B simple_shell
uses the following key functions internally:

.TP
.B handle_input
Captures user input, parses it, and determines the appropriate command to execute.
.TP
.B parse_input
Tokenizes user input into command arguments.
.TP
.B execute_command
Executes the parsed command using fork and execve.
.TP
.B check_exit
Checks if the entered command is `exit` and terminates the shell if true.
.TP
.B _getenv
Retrieves the value of environment variables.
.TP
.B get_file_loc
Determines the full path of an executable file.

.SH RETURN VALUE
.B simple_shell
always returns 0 unless it encounters an unrecoverable error.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B simple_shell
Starts the shell. You can type commands like `ls`, `pwd`, etc., followed by `exit` to terminate.

.SH AUTHORS
Adrian Santiago and Gabriel Rivera
